New Records: Victor Wembanyama scored 10 points, making 4-of-10 field goals and 2-of-6 three-pointers, while grabbing 10 rebounds and blocking three shots.
Three Milwaukee players—Damian Lillard (26), Giannis Antetokounmpo (25), and Brook Lopez (22)—scored at least 22 points.
Key Match Events: The Milwaukee Bucks never trailed after AJ Green's three-pointer with 3:09 left in the first quarter.
The San Antonio Spurs suffered a 16-point loss, their third straight loss, leaving them as the Western Conference No. 10 seed.
Post-Match Reflections: The Spurs' journey back to NBA contention continues to face challenges with this loss.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Milwaukee's field goal percentage was 47.8, compared to San Antonio's 36.8.
